<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/464594-hello-community-it-has-been-suggested-to">Hello community! It has been suggested to me that I should read the introduction of this book before actually reading the book - there are spoilers though. Does anyone advise I read the intro before or after the story itself? Thanks for the help!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_464594'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F29981.The_Island_of_Dr_Moreau">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/464594-hello-community-it-has-been-suggested-to">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/464594-hello-community-it-has-been-suggested-to">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/39346323-greg"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1513962691i/39346323._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/39346323-greg">Greg</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Depends on the edition. If it&apos;s the author&apos;s introduction, absolutely. If it is someone else&apos;s introduction, then that someone might tell you too much<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Depends on the edition. If it's the author's introduction, absolutely. If it is someone else's introduction, then that someone might tell you too much about the story. I make it a point never to read introductions unless they were originally written by the author upon publication of the book. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

