              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12841463547974971060">H.G. Wells truly could see into the future...this book is truly a foreshadowing of some of the bioethical debates going on right now. But the question to my GR friends is: what is more bestial...beasts who must follow &apos;The Law&apos; or men who put beasts into that position? It seems to me that is a question that still echoes into our age.</span>
  <span id="freeText12841463547974971060" style="display:none">H.G. Wells truly could see into the future...this book is truly a foreshadowing of some of the bioethical debates going on right now. But the question to my GR friends is: what is more bestial...beasts who must follow 'The Law' or men who put beasts into that position? It seems to me that is a question that still echoes into our age.</span>
